# Package Installation
Always use PNPM for installing packages with format pnpm install <package> (-d)
e.g.: 
- Production package: `pnpm install react`
- Development package: `pnpm install -d eslint`

**Exception**: When installing PRODUCTION packages specifically for projects located under the `packages/` directory, install the package directly in that project's directory instead of the workspace root.

Examples:
- General workspace dependency: `pnpm install react` (installs in workspace root)
- Package-specific dependency: `cd packages/converter && pnpm install lodash` (installs in packages/converter/)

# Testing Changes
As you iterate towards a solution, you should test your changes using NX workspace commands.
All commands follow the pattern of `pnpm nx <command> <project> <options>`.

Possible commands:
- `typecheck` - Typecheck the project
- `test` - Test the project. Always use the `--watch=false` option.
  - Run tests for a specific file: `pnpm nx test <project> <path-from-PROJECT-root> --watch=false`
    - e.g. `pnpm nx test ui ./app/utils/crypto.utils.test.ts --watch=false`
  - Run tests for a specific test name: `pnpm nx test <project> --testNamePattern=<test-name>`
    - e.g. `pnpm nx test converter --testNamePattern="should parse IFC file"`
- `lint` - Lint the project (runs oxlint then eslint). Paths are relative to the project root.
  - Full project: `pnpm nx lint <project>`
    - e.g. `pnpm nx lint ui`
  - Single file: `pnpm nx lint <project> --files=<path>`
    - e.g. `pnpm nx lint ui --files=app/utils/crypto.utils.ts`
  - Glob pattern: `pnpm nx lint <project> --files='<glob>'`
    - e.g. `pnpm nx lint kernels --files='src/utils/*.ts'`
  - Multiple files: `pnpm nx lint <project> --files='<path1> <path2>'`
    - e.g. `pnpm nx lint kernels --files='src/utils/hash.utils.ts src/utils/edge-detection.ts'`
- `build` - Build the project

The project is the name of the project you are working on, as designated by the path. For example, changes under `apps/ui` correspond to the `ui` project, whilst changes under `packages/converter` correspond to the `converter` project.

A full example to test the `ui` project would be `pnpm nx test ui`.
